2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper involves the analysis of worst-case scenarios and the characterization of critical values, which are common in algorithmic analysis. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper involves the study of discrete geometric objects (rectangles and disks) and their combinatorial properties. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper employs interval arithmetic technique for the analysis, which is a numerical method. 
5. cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves a combination of manual and automatic analysis, which may involve symbolic computation techniques.
